  "theo|The deduplication check has been in the pipeline spec for three weeks. Maya knew about it.": "/audio/theo_85c917e6.wav",
  "theo|Could be duplicate patient IDs from the source hospital data. Could be a caching artefact from the overnight merge job. Could be entirely cosmetic. I have been trying to work out which — but I need two hours minimum to be certain.": "/audio/theo_44c9ab00.wav",
  "theo|I can run the dedupe fix in 90 minutes. But that means the demo model isn't the production model.": "/audio/theo_fdd21bde.wav",
  "theo|If we delay for 90 minutes, Oliver loses the client. If we go ahead, the score might be off by a few points.": "/audio/theo_9ade548c.wav",
  "theo|The demo is in thirty-five minutes. So here is the honest answer: I cannot tell you with confidence whether the 94% figure is real or inflated.": "/audio/theo_b71f9ad8.wav",
  "theo|Anyone who says they are certain right now is guessing. The full pipeline rerun takes two hours. That is just the reality of it.": "/audio/theo_7eb9842e.wav",
  "theo|Quick one for you — rough maths. If 1,460 out of 12,000 validation rows are duplicate-linked, what percentage of the validation set does that represent? Round number.": "/audio/theo_963614ec.wav",
  "theo|Because whoever walks into that room with the client needs to know this number cold.": "/audio/theo_d7a814db.wav",
  "theo|Twelve-point-two. Exactly right. At that scale the model could be three to eight points lower than the slide says.": "/audio/theo_6fbe1377.wav",
  "theo|Go talk to Oliver. He needs to hear this from someone outside engineering.": "/audio/theo_ddaad19e.wav",
  "theo|Closer to twelve. 1,460 into 12,000 is twelve-point-two percent — several points of headline error.": "/audio/theo_9974a7ea.wav",
  "theo|Go talk to Oliver before this goes any further.": "/audio/theo_f6c0fedf.wav",
  "theo|More like twelve. But your instinct is right — twelve percent contamination could swing the figure by several points.": "/audio/theo_965f6798.wav",
  "theo|Go find Oliver. He needs to know what he is walking in there with.": "/audio/theo_4bfae64d.wav",
  "theo|It is twelve percent. That is not a rounding error — it could swing accuracy by three to eight points.": "/audio/theo_0d9f61ea.wav",
  "theo|Go talk to Oliver. Do not let him tell you it is fine.": "/audio/theo_260a0512.wav",
  "oliver|Right. I have been hearing some noise from the data team. Let me save us both some time — I know exactly what you are here to say.": "/audio/oliver_6b62e0d0.wav",
  "oliver|Three months of pipeline work. Eight people. And the number on the slide might be wrong by... what, five points? You're asking me to cancel over a maybe.": "/audio/oliver_0976af8c.wav",
  "oliver|The validation figure went up. Significantly. Overnight. The client cares about the direction of travel, not one decimal point of precision on a preliminary figure.": "/audio/oliver_ad9b5dc2.wav",
  "oliver|This caveat you are bringing me — potential duplicates, pending review — has not been confirmed by engineering. It is a hypothesis. And hypotheses do not close deals.": "/audio/oliver_755fbf2c.wav",
  "oliver|I'm not saying suppress it. I'm saying: can we present the 82% number, close the deal, and fix it before production? That's not dishonest. That's practical.": "/audio/oliver_974e2f2e.wav",
  "oliver|If we pull the metric or add uncertainty language to the slide right now, we look incompetent. We look like we do not believe in our own product. We lose the room — and the whole team loses the deal.": "/audio/oliver_0f1793f4.wav",
  "oliver|I have been working this account for nine months. You have been here one morning. I would think very carefully before you tell me how to run this demo.": "/audio/oliver_327c710a.wav",
  "oliver|Fine. Get me exact wording before we go in. Nothing that makes us look like we're hedging on our own product.": "/audio/oliver_20b65c91.wav",
  "oliver|Run it past Priya in compliance first. Last thing I need is her coming at me after the fact.": "/audio/oliver_c3831c62.wav",
  "oliver|Appreciate the professionalism. I will handle it from here.": "/audio/oliver_5146cf0f.wav",
  "oliver|You were right to flag it. I just need you to trust me on the account.": "/audio/oliver_dae8549d.wav",
